              </strong><strong>Oasis, Boston, MA, February 3, 2005--</strong> The OASIS international standards consortium today announced that its members have approved the Universal Description, Discovery and Integration (UDDI) version 3.0.2 as an OASIS Standard, a status that signifies the highest level of ratification. Advanced through an open process, UDDI is commonly regarded as a cornerstone of Web services, defining a standard method for publishing and discovering network-based software components in a service-oriented architecture (SOA). &quot;The UDDI registry model is one of the central elements of an interoperable framework that ensures the effective interaction of services in a service oriented architecture.&quot; said Frank Kenney, analyst at Gartner. &quot;By enabling policy-based distribution and management of enterprise Web services, a UDDI registry can deliver significant business value. ...<a href="http://www.oasis-open.org/news/oasis_news_02_03_05.php">Full Story </a></p>
